    "body": "## Summary\n\nRestructure the codebase so that each backend (cpu, cuda, rocm) owns its GEMM implementations, sparse GEMM implementations, and transform passes under a consistent `op/` subdirectory layout. The shared GEMM registry and base classes remain in `tileop/` as the platform-agnostic dispatch layer.\n\nThis makes backend ownership explicit: adding a new backend no longer requires modifying shared `transform` or `tileop` modules, and all backend-specific code follows the same symmetric directory structure.\n\n## Changes\n\n### Registry extraction\n- Moved `backend/gemm.py` → `tileop/gemm/registry.py` (GEMM register/resolve)\n- Moved `backend/gemm_sp.py` → `tileop/gemm_sp/registry.py` (sparse GEMM register/resolve)\n\n### CUDA backend\n- `tileop/gemm/gemm_mma.py` → `backend/cuda/op/gemm/gemm_mma.py`\n- `tileop/gemm/gemm_mma_sm70.py` → `backend/cuda/op/gemm/gemm_mma_sm70.py`\n- `tileop/gemm/gemm_wgmma.py` → `backend/cuda/op/gemm/gemm_wgmma.py`\n- `tileop/gemm/gemm_tcgen05.py` → `backend/cuda/op/gemm/gemm_tcgen05.py`\n- `tileop/gemm_sp/gemm_sp_mma.py` → `backend/cuda/op/gemm_sp/gemm_sp_mma.py`\n- Registration files converted to package `__init__.py`\n\n### CPU backend\n- `tileop/gemm/gemm_scalar.py` → `backend/cpu/op/gemm/gemm_scalar.py`\n\n### ROCm backend\n- `tileop/gemm/gemm_mfma.py` → `backend/rocm/op/gemm/gemm_mfma.py`\n- `tileop/gemm/gemm_wmma.py` → `backend/rocm/op/gemm/gemm_wmma.py`\n\n### Transform passes\n- Moved C++ transform sources from `src/transform/` into `src/backend/cuda/transform/`\n- Moved C++ runtime sources from `src/runtime/` into `src/backend/cuda/`\n- Added `backend/cuda/transform/__init__.py` to wrap FFI calls\n- Removed three dead backend-importing wrappers from `transform/__init__.py` (`LowerHopperIntrin`, `LowerL2Persistent`, `PersistThreadblock`)\n\n### Callers\n- Updated `engine/phase.py` and the Hopper intrinsics test to import CUDA transforms from `backend.cuda.transform` directly\n\n### Final structure\n```\nbackend/\n├── cpu/op/gemm/          # __init__.py (registration) + gemm_scalar.py\n├── cuda/op/\n│   ├── gemm/             # __init__.py + mma, mma_sm70, wgmma, tcgen05\n│   └── gemm_sp/          # __init__.py + mma\n└── rocm/op/gemm/         # __init__.py + mfma, wmma\n\ntileop/\n├── gemm/                 # __init__.py (FFI class), gemm_base.py, registry.py\n└── gemm_sp/              # __init__.py (FFI class), gemm_sp_base.py, registry.py\n```\n\n## Test plan\n\n- Run existing GEMM tests (`pytest testing/python/transform/test_tilelang_transform_lower_hopper_intrin.py`)\n- Verify the format check passes (`bash format.sh`)\n- Verify no import errors by checking that all backend modules load correctly\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n## Release Notes\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added CUDA runtime functions for tensor map creation and L2 persistent cache access policy window configuration\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Reorganized backend-specific intrinsics and transformation passes into dedicated CUDA, ROCm, and CPU packages for improved code organization and modularity\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Consolidated sparse tensor core and floating-point 8 examples; removed element-wise add test file\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
